definition:
πέρας, -ατος, τό
 (πέρα, beyond), [in LXX chiefly for קֵץ, קָצָה and cognate forms ;] 
an end, limit, boundary; 
   (a) of space: chiefly in pl., τὰ π. τ. γῆς, Mat.12:42, Luk.11:31; τ. οἰκουμένης, Rom.10:18 (LXX); 
   (b) (opposite to ἀρχή) the end: with genitive, ἀντιλογίας, Heb.6:10.†
 (AS)
